e [[Lumbini Zone]] of southern [[Nepal]]. At the time of the [[1991 Nepal census]] it had a population of 5654 people living in 889 individual households.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/nepalcensus/form.php?selection=1|title=Nepal Census 2001|work=Nepal's Village Development Committees|publisher=[[Digital Himalaya]]|accessdate=18 December 2008 }}</ref> \n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Nawalparasi district data}}\n\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Parasi District]]\n\n\n{{Province5NP-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pegship", "label": "safe", "comment": "update district", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pratappur,_Nepal"}
{"title_page": "Caleb Jones (politician)", "text_new": "{{Infobox state representative\n| honorific-prefix = \n| name         = Caleb Jones\n| honorific-suffix = \n| image        = \n| alt          = \n| title = Deputy Chief of Staff to the [[List_of_Governors_of_Missouri|Governor of Missouri]]\n| term_start   =  January 9, 2017\n| term_end    =  \n| state_house1  =  Missouri\n| district1     =  50th\n| term_start1   =  January 9, 2013\n| term_end1     =  January 9, 2017\n| predecessor1  = Michael R. Brown\n| successor1    =  Sara Walsh\n| state_house2  =  Missouri\n| district2     =  117th\n| term_start2   =  January 5, 2011\n| term_end2     =  January 9, 2013\n| predecessor2  = Kenny Jones\n| successor2    =  [[Linda_Black_(politician)|Linda Black]]\n| prior_term   =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|1|9}}\n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| profession = Attorney\n| party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n}}\n\n'''Caleb Jones''' (born January 9, 1980) is an [[American people|American]] [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] politician. He served as member of the [[Missouri House of Representatives]] from the 50th District, being first elected for the 117th District in 2010.  He then served as Deputy Chief of Staff to Governor Eric Greitens in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Representative Caleb Jones|url=http://www.house.mo.gov/bio.aspx?year=2015&district=050|publisher=Missouri House of Representatives|accessdate=27 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Caleb Jones|url=http://ballotpedia.org/Caleb_Jones|publisher=[[Ballotpedia]]|accessdate=27 April 2015}}</ref> He is currently the CEO for Missouri Electric Cooperatives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amec.org/content/amec-board-and-executive-committee|title=AMEC Board and Executive Committee {{!}} Association of Missouri Electric Cooperatives|website=www.amec.org|access-date=2019-04-25}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n\n== Biography ==\nCaleb grew up in rural Moniteau County, Missouri.  The son of a local Sheriff and school teacher, Caleb attending Clarksburg Elementary School and California High School.  He excelled in academics and sports as student body president, a member of the 1997 Missouri 3A Football Champions, the 1997 FFA Missouri State Star Farmer, as well as a member of Drama Club, National Honor Society, Show Choir and many other organizations.  After high school, Caleb attended the University of Missouri-Columbia majoring in Agricultural Economics in the College of Agriculture, Food and Natural Resources.  \n\n==Electoral History==\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title =2016 General Election for Missouri's 50th District House of Representatives<ref>http://enrarchives.sos.mo.gov/enrnet/default.aspx?eid=750003949</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Caleb Jones \n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 15,705\n| percentage = 100\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 15,705\n| percentage= 100\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title =2014 General Election for Missouri's 50th District House of Representatives<ref>http://enrarchives.sos.mo.gov/enrnet/default.aspx?eid=750003949</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Caleb Jones \n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 7,832\n| percentage = 100\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 7,832\n| percentage= 100\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title =2012 General Election for Missouri's 50th District House of Representatives<ref>http://enrarchives.sos.mo.gov/enrnet/default.aspx?eid=750002497</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Caleb Jones \n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 13,425\n| percentage = 100\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 13,425\n| percentage= 100\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n{{Election box begin no change\n| ti