9, 1980) is an [[American people|American]] [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] politician. He served as member of the [[Missouri House of Representatives]] from the 50th District, being first elected for the 117th District in 2010.  He then served as Deputy Chief of Staff to Governor Eric Greitens in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Representative Caleb Jones|url=http://www.house.mo.gov/bio.aspx?year=2015&district=050|publisher=Missouri House of Representatives|accessdate=27 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Caleb Jones|url=http://ballotpedia.org/Caleb_Jones|publisher=[[Ballotpedia]]|accessdate=27 April 2015}}</ref> He is currently the CEO for Missouri Electric Cooperatives.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amec.org/content/amec-board-and-executive-committee|title=AMEC Board and Executive Committee {{!}} Association of Missouri Electric Cooperatives|website=www.amec.org|access-date=2019-04-25}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n\n== Biography ==\nCaleb grew up in rural Moniteau County, Missouri.  The son of a local Sheriff and school teacher, Caleb attending Clarksburg Elementary School and California High School.  He excelled in academics and sports as Student Body President, a member of the 1997 Missouri 3A Football Champions, the 1997 FFA Missouri State Star Farmer, as well as a member of Drama Club, National Honor Society, Show Choir and many other organizations.  After high school, Caleb attended the University of Missouri-Columbia majoring in Agricultural Economics in the College of Agriculture, Food and Natural Resources.  \n\n==Electoral History==\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title =2016 General Election for Missouri's 50th District House of Representatives<ref>http://enrarchives.sos.mo.gov/enrnet/default.aspx?eid=750003949</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Caleb Jones \n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 15,705\n| percentage = 100\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 15,705\n| perc