{"title_page": "Noriaki Sugiyama", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Noriaki Sugiyama\n| image              = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u6749\u5c71 \u7d00\u5f70\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_place        = [[Tokyo]], Japan<ref name=\"Profile\">{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u6749\u5c71\u3000\u7d00\u5f70\uff5c\u65e5\u672c\u30bf\u30ec\u30f3\u30c8\u540d\u9451 |url=https://www.vip-times.co.jp/?talent_id=M14-0349 |website=[[Nihon Tarento Meikan]] |accessdate=11 October 2018 |language=ja}}</ref>\n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*[[Voice acting in Japan|Voice actor]]\n*narrator\n}}\n| years_active       = 2000\u2013present\n| agent              = Stay-Luck\n| credits            = {{Plainlist|\n*''[[Naruto]]'' as [[Sasuke Uchiha]]\n*''[[Bleach (TV series)|Bleach]]'' as [[Ury\u016b Ishida]]\n*''[[Fate/stay night]]'' as [[Shir\u014d Emiya]]\n}}\n| height             = 168 cm<ref name=\"Profile\" />\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Noriaki Sugiyama'''|\u6749\u5c71 \u7d00\u5f70|''Sugiyama Noriaki''}} is a Japanese [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actor]] and [[narrator]] Born in Tokyo, Japan on March 9 1977.\n\n==Biography==\nSugiyama is the oldest of four siblings. He worked part-time at a gaming company. He is represented by Stay-Luck. He is married since 2009 and has a daughter born the same year.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Anime===\n;2000\n* ''[[Boogiepop Phantom]]'' (Tetsu Yabe)\n\n;2001\n* ''[[Bakuten Shoot Beyblade]]'' (Blader DJ)\n\n;2002\n* ''[[Naruto]]'' ([[Sasuke Uchiha]])\n* ''[[Beyblade: V-Force]]'' (Blader DJ)\n* ''[[Mirage of Blaze]]'' (Additional voice)\n\n;2003\n* ''[[Beyblade G Revolution]]'' (Blader DJ)\n* ''[[Full Metal Panic? Fumoffu]]'' (Crewman)\n* ''[[Dark Shell]]'' (Fukushima)\n\n;2004\n* ''[[Bleach (TV series)|Bleach]]'' ([[Ury\u016b Ishida]])\n\n;2005\n* ''[[The Law of Ueki]]'' ([[List of characters in The Law of Ueki#Ancho Kabara|Ancho Kabara]])\n* ''[[Kamichu!]]'' (Inu-Oshu/dog priest)\n* ''[[Hell Girl]]'' (Mamoru Hanagasa)\n* ''[[Fushigiboshi no Futagohime|Fushigiboshi no Futagohime Gyu!]]'' (Hills)\n* ''[[Damekko D\u014dbutsu]]'' (Usahara)\n\n;2006\n* ''[[The Story of Saiunkoku]]'' ([[List of The Story of Saiunkoku characters#Sh\u014drin|Sh\u014drin]], S\u00e2nta)\n* ''[[Code Geass|Code Geass: Lelouch of the Rebellion]]'' ([[Rivalz Cardemonde]], [[List of Code Geass characters#The Order of the Black Knights|Kento Sugiyama]])\n* ''[[Fate/stay night]]'' ([[Shir\u014d Emiya]])\n* ''[[Gintama]]'' (Sniper Kame)\n\n;2007\n* ''[[Toward the Terra]]'' (Tony)\n* ''[[\u014ckiku Furikabutte]]'' (Junta Takase)\n* ''[[Naruto Shippuden]]'' (Sasuke Uchiha)\n* ''[[Koutetsu Sangokushi]]'' (Chouun Shiryuu)\n* ''[[Moyashimon]]'' (Takuma Kawahama)\n\n;2008\n* ''[[Black Butler]]'' (William T. Spears)\n* ''[[Code Geass|Code Geass: Lelouch of the Rebellion R2]]'' ([[Rivalz Cardemonde]], [[List of Code Geass characters#The Order of the Black Knights|Kento Sugiyama]])\n\n;2009\n* ''[[Hetalia: Axis Powers]]'' ([[List of Hetalia: Axis Powers characters#Britain|England]])\n* ''[[Beyblade: Metal Fusion]]'' (Blader DJ)\n\n;2010\n* ''[[Hetalia: World Series]]'' (England)\n* ''[[Beyblade: Metal Masters]]'' (Blader DJ)\n* ''[[Shukufuku no Campanella]]'' (Aberdeen Roland)\n* ''[[Stitch!|Stitch! ~Zutto Saik\u014d no Tomodachi~]]'' (Wishy-Washy, Slushy, Student A)\n* ''[[Black Butler]]'' II (William T. Spears)\n\n;2011\n* ''[[Beyblade Metal Fury]]'' (Blader DJ)\n* ''[[Cardfight!! Vanguard]]'' (Katsumi Morikawa)\n* ''[[Carnival Phantasm]]'' ([[Shir\u014d Emiya]])\n* ''[[Nyanpire]]'' (Masamunya Dokuganryu)\n\n;2012\n* ''[[Moyashimon|Moyasimon Returns]]'' (Takuma Kawahama)\n* ''[[Kimi to Boku (manga)|Kimi to Boku. 2]]'' (Akihiro)\n* ''[[Hagure Yuusha no Estetica]]'' (Phil Barnett)\n\n;2013\n